# Arduino Traffic Light System

## Project Description

This project demonstrates a basic traffic light using Arduino Uno and three LEDs.

The system cycles through:

- Red Light (Stop)
- Green Light (Go)
- Yellow Light (Wait)

The sequence repeats continuously.

---

## Components

- Arduino Uno
- Breadboard
- Red LED
- Yellow LED
- Green LED
- 3 × 220Ω Resistors
- Jumper Wires
- USB Cable

---

## Connections

Red LED → Pin 8

Yellow LED → Pin 9

Green LED → Pin 10

All LED negative terminals connect to GND through 220Ω resistors.

---

## Software

- Arduino IDE

---

## Upload Steps

1. Connect Arduino.
2. Open Arduino IDE.
3. Select Arduino Uno.
4. Select COM Port.
5. Paste the code.
6. Click Upload.

---

## Working

The Red LED glows for 5 seconds.

Then the Green LED glows for 5 seconds.

Then the Yellow LED glows for 2 seconds.

The cycle repeats continuously.

